clfs = []
tree_node_count = []
max_depth = []

for ccp_alpha in ccp_alphas:
    clf = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=0, ccp_alpha=ccp_alpha)
    clf.fit(X_train, y_train)
    clfs.append(clf)
    test_predictions = clf.predict(X_test)
    error_rate.append(1-accuracy_score(y_test,test_predictions))
    tree_node_count.append(clf.tree_.node_count)
    max_depth.append(clf.tree_.max_depth)
cost_complexity_dict = {'alpha_eff':ccp_alphas,'node_count':tree_node_count, 'max_depth':max_depth, 'error_rate': error_rate}

Cross validation with cost complexity pruning¶

In [98]:
def run_cross_validation_on_trees(X, y, ccp_alphas, cv=5, scoring='accuracy'):
    cv_scores_list = []
    cv_scores_std = []
    cv_scores_mean = []
    accuracy_scores = []
    for ccp_alpha in ccp_alphas:
        tree_model = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=0, ccp_alpha=ccp_alpha)
        cv_scores = cross_val_score(tree_model, X, y, cv=cv, scoring=scoring)
        cv_scores_list.append(cv_scores)
        cv_scores_mean.append(cv_scores.mean())
        cv_scores_std.append(cv_scores.std())
        accuracy_scores.append(tree_model.fit(X, y).score(X, y))
    cv_scores_mean = np.array(cv_scores_mean)
    cv_scores_std = np.array(cv_scores_std)
    accuracy_scores = np.array(accuracy_scores)
    return cv_scores_mean, cv_scores_std, accuracy_scores
In [345]:
def plot_cross_validation_on_trees(ccp_alphas, cv_scores_mean, cv_scores_std, accuracy_scores, title):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1, figsize=(15,5))
    ax.plot(ccp_alphas, cv_scores_mean, '-o', label='mean cross-validation accuracy', alpha=0.9)
#     ax.fill_between(ccp_alphas, cv_scores_mean-2*cv_scores_std, cv_scores_mean+2*cv_scores_std, alpha=0.2)
#     ylim = plt.ylim()
    ax.plot(ccp_alphas, accuracy_scores, '-*', label='train accuracy', alpha=0.9)
    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=16)
    ax.set_xlabel('effective alpha', fontsize=14)
    ax.set_ylabel('Accuracy', fontsize=14)
#     ax.set_ylim(ylim)
#     ax.set_xticks(ccp_alphas)
    ax.legend()

alphas = []

    df = cost_complexity_df.loc[cost_complexity_df['max_depth'] == depth]
    min_id = df['mse'].idxmin()
    alpha_eff = df.loc[min_id]['alpha_eff']
    alphas.append(alpha_eff)
if not alphas.count(0):
    alphas.insert(0,0)

Cross Validation for pruning¶

In [280]:
def run_cross_validation_on_regression_trees(X, y, ccp_alphas, cv=5, scoring='neg_mean_squared_error'):
    cv_scores_list = []
    cv_scores_std = []
    cv_scores_mean = []
    accuracy_scores = []
    for ccp_alpha in ccp_alphas:
        tree_model = DecisionTreeRegressor(random_state=0, ccp_alpha=ccp_alpha)
        cv_scores = cross_val_score(tree_model, X, y, cv=cv, scoring=scoring)
        cv_scores_list.append(cv_scores)
        cv_scores_mean.append(-cv_scores.mean())
        cv_scores_std.append(cv_scores.std())
        
        
#         print(mean_squared_error(tree_model.fit(X, y).predict(X),test_predictions))
        accuracy_scores.append(mean_squared_error(tree_model.fit(X, y).predict(X),test_predictions))
    cv_scores_mean = np.array(cv_scores_mean)
    cv_scores_std = np.array(cv_scores_std)
    accuracy_scores = np.array(accuracy_scores)
    return cv_scores_mean, cv_scores_std, accuracy_scores
In [281]:
def plot_cross_validation_on_regression_trees(ccp_alphas, cv_scores_mean, cv_scores_std, accuracy_scores, title):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1, figsize=(15,5))
    ax.plot(ccp_alphas, cv_scores_mean, '-o', label='mean cross-validation r^2', alpha=0.9)
#     ax.fill_between(ccp_alphas, cv_scores_mean-2*cv_scores_std, cv_scores_mean+2*cv_scores_std, alpha=0.2)
    ylim = plt.ylim()
    ax.plot(ccp_alphas, accuracy_scores, '-*', label='train r^2', alpha=0.9)
    ax.set_title(title, fontsize=16)
    ax.set_xlabel('effective alpha', fontsize=14)
    ax.set_ylabel('r^2', fontsize=14)
    ax.set_ylim(ylim)
#     ax.set_xticks(ccp_alphas)
    ax.legend()

9 c/d) Detailed tree output/ Plot of the tree¶

In [326]:
dot_data = tree.export_graphviz(clf, out_file=None,
                               feature_names=X.columns,

graph
Out[326]:

The baseline classification decision tree in scikit-learn created nodes until each terminal node gini value was as small as possible. So in this case there were many terminal nodes with only a few samples in each. Therefor the information in each of these nodes shows the gini coefficient (typically 0 in this tree), the number of samples, and the class. This is likely an over fit.
